          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>החיים והשלום ??? ונצחיות לידיד ד וי"נ ולבי ה"ה</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>האלוף כלתו כמהורר לידר יאיר לנוף</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>Revd</p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Yiddish-Hebrew</hi>
                                        </add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>July 17,
                                                  1849</date>.</p>
                              <p>Life and peace to my friend <addressee>Rabbi
                                        Leeser</addressee>.....</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">We have dared to go into the holy courts<lb/> of
                                        God and pray that he might grant to you, whose<lb/> name is
                                        well known in Judah and <placeName>Israel</placeName>, long
                                        life.<lb/> I have presumed to speak, and send my words
                                        to<lb/> you. I have heard through <persName>Mr.
                                                  Morrison</persName> that you<lb/> will be good
                                        enough to listen to my words, and I<lb/> therefore gave him
                                        $15 with the earnest decision, <del>that</del><lb/> at the
                                        end of two months, to give you more until I<lb/> complete my
                                        payments. But now <del>my</del> I am afraid<lb/> I know very
                                        well all the good you have done for me,<lb/> from the
                                        beginnings to this day. And now I am in<lb/> danger of being
                                        caught in a transgression; not to be<lb/> able to fulfill my
                                        promise. For the cause of the<lb/> difficulties of the time
                                        and the confusion caused by<lb/> the cholera, not only has
                                        the money and means of a<lb/> livelihood decreased, but
                                        there is a lack of the utmost<lb/> necessities. That is the
                                        reason why my soul weeps<lb/> in hiding and I am concerned
                                        lest, much to my<lb/> regret and pain, I be unable to
                                        fulfill, on the<lb/> appointed day, that to which I see
                                        myself ob-<lb/>ligated and I should very much like to
                                        accomplish.<lb/> I am anxious that you should think bitterly
                                        of me,<lb/> for he, who knows the hidden secrets of the
                                        heart, to him<lb/> it is clear that my thought and desire is
                                        to pay,<lb/> God willing. Only one thing I ask of you, to
                                        give<lb/> permission to <persName>Mr. Morrison</persName> to
                                        wait a few weeks<lb/> until the disturbance caused by the
                                        sickness<lb/> passes. For, thank God, I have received news
                                        from<lb/> all my customers who have for years lodged<lb/>
                                        with me, to hold their rooms in readiness<lb/> for them.
                                        They expect to come, at the latest,</p>
                              <pb n="5"/>
                              <p>towards the end of <date>August</date>. And, if it<lb/> will be the
                                        will of the Creator, to send his<lb/> complete cure even
                                        sooner, and if he will<lb/> remove his anger from us, They
                                        will come<lb/> here earlier. I stretch my hand out to<lb/>
                                        you and hope<add>?</add> that for God's sake you do not<lb/>
                                        judge me harshly, and to extend my<lb/> term for another
                                        four to six weeks. Be-<lb/>cause of this our Father in
                                        heaven will<lb/> lengthen your days and your years in<lb/>
                                        goodness and sweetness. And nay this<lb/> be this will.
                                        Amen.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My wife and sons, long life to them,<lb/> send you
                                        greetings, and especially my<lb/> son
                                                  <persName>Nathan</persName>. Etc.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">With greetings of Peace,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Your friend, who waits for your aid,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">____________________</p>
                              <p>P. S. If you will honor me with an answer,<lb/> it will be like
                                        cool water for a tired spirit.<lb/> My address is <persName
                                                  role="author">L. Solomon</persName>
                                        <placeName>250 William St.<lb/> N.Y.</placeName></p>
                    </body>
